    <abstract>
      <para>Snail and slug abundance were measured for a 10 year
      period between 1997 - 2006 at three elevations on Watershed 1
      as well as in a reference area west of Watershed 6. Watershed
      1 received calcium additions as wollastonite (CaSiO3) during
      the study period. This data set includes counts of snails and
      and slugs for the entire study period.</para>
      <para>These data were gathered as part of the Hubbard Brook
      Ecosystem Study (HBES). The HBES is a collaborative effort at
      the Hubbard Brook Experimental Forest, which is operated and
      maintained by the USDA Forest Service, Northern Research
      Station.</para>
    </abstract>
